    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-11-23T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-11-23T18:00:00-05:00" n="312"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d312">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.77/226a</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul at Vladivostok</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_CJK1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caldwell</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-11-23T18:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 23, 1917, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">Brooklyn</hi> due Vladivostok November 25. Department advised
                    rumor recurrent Siberia that work of <persName corresp="#p_SJF1"
                        >Stevens</persName> is merely entering wedge for absorption of railway by
                    United States and that arrival Russian Railway Service Corps under <persName
                        corresp="#p_ECH1">Emerson</persName> may be interpreted as further step same
                    direction.</p>
                <pb facs="0259" n="209" xml:id="pg_209"/>
                <p>If inquiries are made of you, you are authorized to say in reply: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>
                            <persName corresp="#p_SJF1">Stevens</persName> railway commission and
                                <persName corresp="#p_ECH1">Emerson</persName> railway service corps
                            organized at considerable sacrifice to railways of United States for
                            sole purpose to assist Russia in her need and without any connection
                            whatsoever with financial assistance which has been given by United
                            States.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_ECH1">Emerson</persName> and his corps sailed for
                    Vladivostok November 18. <persName corresp="#p_SJF1">Stevens</persName> reported
                        <hi rend="italic">en route</hi> to meet them there.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
